cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.SY

This paper deals with the analysis and mitigation of botnet formation in wireless IoT networks, which involves network security, communication networks, and system dynamics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses malware infiltration and coordination, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of optimization techniques for network defense suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the analysis of mean-field equilibrium and point process theory relates to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
